reviews.text: Best Chicken leg in town. Owned by a Japanese couple, who are really giving their ALL. Great quality food. Recommend!
Delicious iberico ham lobster soup ramen. Next time I will try the chicken legs.😝

This restaurant was terrible in every way. 
Firstly we were only given one menu the waiter then disappeared. I had to get up to get a second menu myself. 
Both menus  were confusing and different eg clip in pages were in random order. 
We ordered a French bottle of wine. Ps the only French thing about this restaurant. At $600 HKD a bottle it was warm eg wasn’t kept a wine fridge just straight from the cupboard. The wine glasses had smudges on them.  The waiter had no idea how to open or pour it. He rested the bottle on the glass as he poured it. We took over the pouring from then on as he didn’t comeback or offer again. 
No offer of water or anything else etc. 
The appetizers came. The oysters dish was terrible it was warm. Not raw or cooked a weird inbetween with no taste. 
At the end of the appetizers after sitting there for a while the waiter  came and asked when we would like our mains ??? Really after our appetizers. !!
No other service eg pouring wine our selfs until the mains came. They came in a small frying pan. I had the chicken my girl friend had the pork chop. They were both just ok. Slightly over cooked.  But what was crazy is they brought out the sauces about 5 mins later to ask which one we would like poured in the pan which had already cooled by now. So they then proceeded to pour a cold sauce on a cooling dish ??  
We had ordered a side of rice which never came. When I asked about it half way through the mains we never heard back and never got it. 
I asked if we could have some water. About 10 min later they brought us 2 glass of hot water eg steaming hot. 
After this we finished and left ASAP. We were charged 10% service charge even on the wine. But really there was no service at all. 
I would never go back again. We should have walked out half way through but thought it would be to rude. Hmm.
Cozy restaurant friendly service and quality food. Reasonable priced. Definitely worth visiting!
Yummy place with comfort food!!!! ❤️

reviews.text: Best Chicken leg in town. Owned by a Japanese couple, who are really giving their ALL. Great quality food. Recommend!
應該晚上是法國菜而中午時間租給一對夫婦主理，太太是日本人，所以用餐時要有心理準備比較慢(人手唔夠)。雞脾飯必食，另龍蝦湯拉麵也好味， 材料新鮮 、用心製作 。
特色日式西餐，好吃的拉麵
일본인 주인 분께서 운영하시는 친절한 프랑스 퓨전 레스토랑입니다. 저희는 저녁식사 후라 아사히 생맥주 하나씩 야외테이블에서 한잔씩 하고 있어요. 일본 특유의 아자기기함이 곳곳에 묻어나네요.
Delicious iberico ham lobster soup ramen. Next time I will try the chicken legs.😝
